Liverpool manager, Jurgen Klopp, on Monday night said he was proud after winning the FIFA Best Coach of the Year award. DAILY POST reports that Klopp won the prize on Monday night at the Teatro alla Scala in Milan, Italy ahead of Manchester City boss, Pep Guardiola and Tottenham coach, Muaricio Pochettino. Speaking after receiving the award, Klopp said at the award ceremony: “It is great, nobody expected this 20, 10, five, four years ago that I would be standing here. “We know what an incredible job you [Mauricio Pochettino] did and what Pep did. I have to say thank you to my outstanding club Liverpool FC. “To the owners thank you, they gave me an incredible team. I have to thank my team – as a coach you can only be as good as your team is. “I’m really proud of being manager of such an incredible bunch of players.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.